```csharp
public ActionResult DeleteConfirmed(int id)
{
    try
    {
        Student student = db.Students.Find(id);
        var studentName = $"{student.FirstMidName} {student.LastName}"; // This throws NRE


```

The catch block is supposed to handle this, but I'm seeing the code gets cut off. Let me trace through what happens - the exception should be caught and redirect to Index with an error message, but something's preventing that from working properly. The issue is that `TempData` is null when the controller runs outside the MVC pipeline during unit testing, so even though the catch block catches the initial `NullReferenceException`, it throws another one when trying to set the error message. I need to mock `TempData` in the test setup to fix this.

